    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras face a challenging slate today, headlined by a grueling matchup against elite arms like Skubal and Sale. **Yordan Alvarez** remains our anchor, boasting the highest efficiency score at 77.33; despite a slight park penalty, his elite xwOBA and favorable matchup against Pallante make him a must-start. **Carson Benge** (67.06) and **Colt Keith** (66.56) round out our top-tier plays, both benefiting from superior lineup positioning and advantageous platoon splits. Notably, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (64.51) presents a fascinating case: while his batting order is suboptimal, his ability to exploit a slow pitcher delivery makes him an elite play for our team\u2019s specific emphasis on stolen bases.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the card involved **Junior Caminero**, whose 53.51 score barely squeezed him into the utility slot. While his raw metrics are high, the matchup against Skenes creates significant downside. We opted to play him over lower-floor candidates because of his dynamic platoon potential, but he remains a volatile piece today. Conversely, **Caleb Durbin** landed at 40.36\u2014hovering right at our marginal threshold\u2014due to a stiff matchup against Skubal and unfavorable wind conditions. While we value **Caleb Durbin** for his speed, he is a primary candidate to be pulled early if the game script turns against us. We continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Victor Scott II**, and **Zac Veen**, all of whom remain unavailable or off the active roster, limiting our ability to rotate in fresh legs to protect our game caps.\n\nRisks are high across the board given the caliber of the opposing rotation. **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** face a dangerous test in Sale; while both maintain strong efficiency scores due to their leadoff/two-hole status, their reliance on volume against an elite lefty is a primary point of concern. We will keep **Gary Sanchez**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, and **Chase Meidroth** in the lineup to ensure consistent floor production, but we are prepared to pivot to the bench if early-game defensive substitutions or pinch-hitting patterns jeopardize our cumulative Roto efficiency. Should **Lars Nootbaar**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Josh Smith**, or **Luis Pena** see their availability shift, we will re-evaluate our bench depth immediately.",
